---
description: Consistent Markdown structure for docs and READMEs
globs: "**/*.{md,mdx}"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Markdown

- One H1; then `##` / `###`—no skipped levels. Sentence-case headings.
- Lists: `-` unordered; indent nested with 2 spaces; numbers only when order matters.
- Fenced blocks with language tags; **inline code** for paths/commands/identifiers.
- Links `[text](url)`—no bare URLs; relative in-repo, absolute external.
- Bold sparingly; no ALL CAPS. Blank line before/after headings, lists, fences, tables. Single trailing newline.

README: title, summary, quickstart, example, config, scripts, contributing/license pointers.
